6static int
7stash_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
8{
9 struct stash_options opt;
10 int ret;
11 int optidx = 0;
12 struct getargs args[] = {
13 { "enctype", 'e', arg_string, NULL, "encryption type", NULL },
14 { "key-file", 'k', arg_string, NULL, "master key file", "file" },
15 { "convert-file", 0, arg_flag, NULL, "just convert keyfile to new format", NULL },
16 { "random-password", 0, arg_flag, NULL, "use a random password (and print the password to stdout)", NULL },
17 { "master-key-fd", 0, arg_integer, NULL, "filedescriptor to read passphrase from", "fd" },
18 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
19 };
20 int help_flag = 0;
21 opt.enctype_string = (char *)(unsigned long)"des3-cbc-sha1";
22 opt.key_file_string = NULL;
23 opt.convert_file_flag = 0;
24 opt.random_password_flag = 0;
25 opt.master_key_fd_integer = -1;
26 args[0].value = &opt.enctype_string;
27 args[1].value = &opt.key_file_string;
28 args[2].value = &opt.convert_file_flag;
29 args[3].value = &opt.random_password_flag;
30 args[4].value = &opt.master_key_fd_integer;
31 args[5].value = &help_flag;
32 if(getarg(args, 6, argc, argv, &optidx))
33 goto usage;
34 if(help_flag)
35 goto usage;
36 ret = stash(&opt, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
37 return ret;
38usage:
39 arg_printusage (args, 6, "stash", "");
40 return 0;
41}

644 if(argc - optidx != 0) {
645 fprintf(stderr, "Need exactly 0 parameters (%u given).\n\n", argc - optidx);
646 goto usage;
647 }
648 if(help_flag)
649 goto usage;
650 ret = lock(NULL, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
651 return ret;
652usage:
653 arg_printusage (args, 1, "lock", "");
654 return 0;
655}

682static int
683help_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
684{
685 int ret;
686 int optidx = 0;
687 struct getargs args[] = {
688 { "help", 'h', arg_flag, NULL, NULL, NULL }
689 };
690 int help_flag = 0;
691 args[0].value = &help_flag;
692 if(getarg(args, 1, argc, argv, &optidx))
693 goto usage;
694 if(argc - optidx > 1) {
695 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are more than expected (1).\n\n", argc - optidx);
696 goto usage;
697 }
698 if(argc - optidx < 0) {
699 fprintf(stderr, "Arguments given (%u) are less than expected (0).\n\n", argc - optidx);
700 goto usage;
701 }
702 if(help_flag)
703 goto usage;
704 ret = help(NULL, argc - optidx, argv + optidx);
705 return ret;
706usage:
707 arg_printusage (args, 1, "help", "[command]");
708 return 0;
709}

712exit_wrap(int argc, char **argv)
713{
714 int ret;
715 int optidx = 0;
716 struct getargs args[] = {
